In article <EACHUS.94Jan5171012@spectre.mitre.org>,
eachus@spectre.mitre.org (Robert I. Eachus) wrote:
>      A) OTP xor PK bit-stream
>      B) OTP xor message
> 
>      A xor B) message xor PK bit-stream

I believe the original poster intended to send the OTP
encrypted by some system like PGP, and then send the
message encrypted by xor against the OTP.  He wants
to know if it is harder to decrypt a random PGP message
vs. a regular plaintext PGP message.  (or other cryptsystem,
public key for convenience in key management).
